dmenu - dynamic menu
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu you need the Xlib header files.
If you want to display unicode character you need patched version of libxft with glyphs / colored emoji rendering (libxft-bgra).
Or you can disable this feature by uncommenting lines from 143 to 149 in drw.c.

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install

Patches included
----------------
* password
* xresources
* line height
* xyw

Running dmenu
-------------
See the man page for details.
